Subsistence agriculture is agriculture that is carried out for the production of sufficient food to only meet the needs of the farmer and his/her family.
Subsistence agriculture is a simple and often organic system that uses stored seeds native to the ecoregion, in combination with crop rotation or other relatively simple techniques, to maximize yield.
Historically, most farmers have been engaged in subsistence agriculture, and this is still the case in many developing countries.
Subcultures bring together like-minded individuals who feel overlooked by societal standards and enable them to develop a sense of identity.
