The official currency of the Falkland Islands is the Falkland Spun (FKP), the value of which is fixed at the value of a British pound (GBP).
Money can be exchanged in the only bank on the islands located in Stanley opposite the FIC West store.
The British pounds are accepted everywhere on the islands, and within Stanley credit cards and US dollars are also often accepted.
On the outlying islands, credit cards are unlikely to be used, even though British and American currencies may be able to be used; ask the owners in advance to know what payment method is accepted.
It is almost impossible to exchange Falkland’s currency outside the islands, so be sure to exchange your money before you leave the islands.
